The paper deals with predicting the temporal dynamics of information diffusion in social networks, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science. The most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), which specifically deals with the analysis of social networks and the spread of information within them. The second most likely sub-category is cs.SD (Software Development and Programming), as the paper describes a graph-based approach and uses machine learning techniques to estimate parameters. The third most likely sub-category is cs.SOC (Computational Social Science), which focuses on the application of computational methods to social science research. The fourth most likely sub-category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval), as the paper deals with predicting the spread of information. The fifth most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper uses machine learning techniques to estimate parameters.
